      • getValue

        public java.lang.Object getValue(java.lang.String str)

        Deprecated. 
        Retrieves a value from python. If the result is not a Java object, the implementation currently returns a String. Python is pretty picky about what it expects here. The general syntax: 
         eval("a = 5")
String a = (String) getValue("a")
        will work.
